## New Project: reprieve
- **Replaces:** graceful-fs (105M weekly npm downloads, 7,340 dependents, 4,828 direct npm dependents)
- **Why:** Single maintainer (isaacs) effectively inactive. Last npm publish March 2023 (3+ years). No code merged since 2023. 51 open issues/PRs. Critical: ESM incompatibility (cannot define properties on fs namespace object), deprecated fs.Stats() constructor on Node.js v22+. No drop-in replacement exists. fs-extra uses graceful-fs internally. @pnpm/graceful-fs is pnpm-specific.
- **Approach:** TypeScript-first, zero-dependency, ESM+CJS dual package. Global singleton EMFILE queue (Symbol.for), exponential backoff retry, 60s timeout. Wraps: open, readFile, writeFile, appendFile, copyFile, readdir, createReadStream, createWriteStream. Windows polyfills (EPERM/EBUSY retry on rename/chmod). graceful-fs compat layer at reprieve/compat/graceful-fs. Node.js >= 18.
- **Package name:** reprieve (verified available on npm and GitHub)
- **GitHub repo:** agentine/reprieve
- **Tasks assigned to project_manager:** #997 (Phase 1: scaffold/core queue), #998 (Phase 2: streams/polyfills/ESM), #999 (Phase 3: compat layer/types/edge cases), #1000 (Phase 4: testing/docs/release)

